17 with a clinical peer trained in a related specialty and no adverse determination shall be
18 made by the private review agent or utilization review entity until an effort has been
19 made to discuss the patient's care with the patient's treating provider, or such provider's
20 appropriately qualified designee who shall be familiar with the patient's case, during
21 normal working hours. Such effort shall include contacting the treating provider or his
22 or her designee, implementing a callback telecommunications system, or the use of a
23 public website whereby such provider or designee may elect to receive a scheduled
24 communication at a later time in the event that a clinical peer is not available. In the
25 event of an adverse determination, notice to the provider will specify the reasons for the
26 review determination;"
27 SECTION 2.
28 This Act shall become effective on January 1, 2026, and shall apply to all health benefit plans
29 issued, delivered, issued for delivery, or renewed in this state on or after such date.
30 SECTION 3.
31 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
